\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Chapters 5 and 6 investigated fire weather variability in Victoria, Australia.
 This research used the McArthur Forest Fire Danger Index (FFDI) to represent
 fire weather.
 The chapters also describe the development of the Victorian Seasonal Bushfire
 Index (VSBI).
 The VSBI is a forecasting tool and alternative fire weather metric.
 The last two chapters also examined climate-bushfire relationships in Victoria.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This chapter investigates fire weather in Ecuador.
 The analyses use some of the methods applied for Victoria.
 The investigation examines if the FFDI can accurately represent fire weather
 in Ecuador.
 The study of fire weather changes in this region used this index.
 Additionally, this research explores the relationship between ENSO and
 fire weather.
 Finally, it assessed if the 20CR and ERA-20C reanalyses capture the observed
 fire weather variability.
 
\end_layout

