\begin_layout Section
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The FFDI is a useful metric of fire danger in the Ecuadorian Andes.
 The index represented as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

high
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 fire danger months those considered to be of greater fire activity (JAS).
 It also showed that October and November can also be dangerous.
 Additionally, the FFDI shows that 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

El Niño
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 events are linked to higher fire danger in this region.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The FFDI results showed that the Ecuadorian Andes experience higher fire
 danger from July to November.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Estacio2012"

\end_inset

 reports that JAS is the typical fire occurrence season in the city of Quito.
 This is the capital of the country and where more information about bushfires
 is available.
 Quito is located in the northern Ecuadorian Andes.
 Therefore, the fire reporting could be biased towards this region.
 In fact, there is scarce information about fire occurrences in other regions
 of the Ecuadorian Andes which might occur in October and November.
 In contrast, other reports argue that during these months fire activity
 does occur (with less intensity) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "SecretariadeAmbiente2013"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results using the FFDI do not show that the year 2012 experienced high
